Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.88,0:00:08.21,sign_22_1_Four_years_ago__,Signs,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1497,1)}Four years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.18,0:00:08.21,sign_53_2_Back_when_the_da,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2491,1)}Back when the darkness of night \Nwas a far {\c&H3B3BBD&}bluer {\c&HFFFFFF&} hue than now...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.44,0:00:20.25,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Odasaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.80,0:00:27.45,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.24,0:00:31.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You're calling a cat Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.05,0:00:33.96,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't he look wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.96,0:00:36.58,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,He gives up his seat when \NI have guests, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.58,0:00:39.42,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you have to hear this, Odasaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.75,0:00:42.47,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,There was a shootout today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.47,0:00:43.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.39,0:00:45.18,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I was trading shots in a warehouse block
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.18,0:00:48.64,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,with an energetic crew armed with \Na machine-gun equipped truck!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.31,0:00:51.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.97,0:00:55.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,And what's with your new injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.26,0:00:58.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Is that from this shootout?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.06,0:01:01.88,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I had to go pee in the midst of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.14,0:01:04.48,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,then I tripped on a ditch \Nbecause I was in such a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.12,0:01:06.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.61,0:01:08.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,When you rush, it's hard to avoid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.09,0:01:10.71,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.51,0:01:13.95,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Dazai Osamu...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.32,0:01:17.18,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,An executive in the Port Mafia, \Na criminal organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.70,0:01:19.18,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, as for the other guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.18,0:01:22.42,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,they ran away crying after I set a \Ntrap and roughed them up a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.79,0:01:25.67,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They're a pretty sorry bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.86,0:01:27.89,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to them, yet again\N I couldn't manage to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.49,0:01:31.05,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,There's a saying among the Port Mafia...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.51,0:01:34.06,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,The biggest misfortune for Dazai's enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.06,0:01:36.11,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,is that they are {\i0}Dazai's {\i1}enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.90,0:01:39.84,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,His list of deeds writ in darkness and blood
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.84,0:01:42.31,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,is enough to make even those \Nin the Mafia tremble.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.70,0:01:45.75,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,He was practically born to be one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.12,0:01:48.02,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.02,0:01:51.88,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if there is a simple, reliable \Nway to commit suicide somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.88,0:01:52.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.14,0:01:54.32,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.97,0:01:59.18,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Man fears death and yet, at the \Nsame time, man is drawn to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.02,0:02:05.72,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Death is endlessly consumed by \Nmen in cities and in literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.33,0:02:09.57,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It is a singular event in one's \Nlife that none may reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.51,0:02:12.91,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That is what I desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.81,0:02:17.46,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,So on that note, barkeep, can \NI have a cup of detergent?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.46,0:02:18.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have any.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.58,0:02:19.96,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.74,0:02:22.83,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about a detergent-based cocktail?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.99,0:02:24.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Bar,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have any.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.15,0:02:26.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there's nothing \Nyou can do about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.24,0:02:29.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku-san, you should've called him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.12,0:02:34.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you never do \Nthat Dazai-kun goes off the rails.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.49,0:02:35.41,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Ango!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.72,0:02:39.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,You should call him out with just about the \Nforce of a hammer hitting the back of his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.93,0:02:42.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I'm driving today, so tomato juice, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.22,0:02:43.86,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.13,0:02:45.21,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Are you on your way back from a job?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.61,0:02:47.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,It was a bad day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.84,0:02:50.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,It took way too much time \Nto buy smuggled items.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:52.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,After haggling until eight,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.09,0:02:54.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,all I have to show for my \Nefforts is this antique watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.36,0:02:59.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}This concludes about 74% \Nof transactions for this quarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.18,0:03:00.54,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Sakaguchi Ango.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:02.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If I account for the 8% \Nof existing organizations
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.98,0:03:03.29,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,He is one of the Port Mafia's \Nintelligence officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.24,0:03:03.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}with which we've never had \Nany transactions,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.95,0:03:06.50,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Almost all critical and \Nclassified information
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.95,0:03:09.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}our profit has exceeded \Nlast year's by 34%.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:09.40,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,pass through Ango when\N communicating with outsiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.07,0:03:12.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Perhaps it is thanks to our youngest \Nexecutive in the organization's history.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.92,0:03:14.80,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,His head's full of information about the \NPort Mafia that's more valuable than gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.22,0:03:13.32,Stray Dogs - Default,{\an8}D,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.62,0:03:18.68,Stray Dogs - Default,{\an8}Ango,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Of course, this summation includes \Ntoday's disastrous deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.99,0:03:17.32,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,There must be as many enemy organizations \Nas there are stars in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.32,0:03:18.71,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,who wish to torture him for information.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.91,0:03:21.47,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,It's a job that requires considerable grit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.91,0:03:24.75,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,So Ango fuzzed his job, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.92,0:03:26.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,"Fuzzed"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.00,0:03:27.91,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we're fuzz buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.08,0:03:32.35,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, it's been a long time \Nsince we first became drinking buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.90,0:03:35.80,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But I've never heard you \Ncomplain about work, Odasaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.80,0:03:37.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,It'd only bore you to hear my stories
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.86,0:03:40.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,as the lowest-ranking member \Nof the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.73,0:03:43.03,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,There you go being secretive again...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.27,0:03:44.74,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you do this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.04,0:03:47.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I punished a kid stealing from a store
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.84,0:03:50.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,in a shopping district that\N pays us protection money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.61,0:03:53.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I mediated a tense face-off between \Nthe lover and the wife of one of our
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.72,0:03:55.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,shell company executives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.19,0:03:59.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Lastly, I disposed of a dud that was found \Nbehind one of the Mafia offices.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.09,0:04:00.45,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Odasaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.45,0:04:02.34,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Let's change jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.34,0:04:04.49,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I want to dispose of duds, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.49,0:04:06.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't be able to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.34,0:04:07.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you'd get blown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.66,0:04:08.93,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Blown up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.93,0:04:10.26,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did you hear that, Ango?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.26,0:04:11.20,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,He said blown up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:13.00,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'd get blown up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.69,0:04:16.83,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,The kind of jobs that come my \Nway as the lowest-ranking member
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.00,0:04:14.49,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8} How far will I get blown away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.49,0:04:15.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.91,0:04:19.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If you'd like, I can blow you up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.83,0:04:19.36,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,are all crap jobs no one\N wants to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.18,0:04:20.75,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8} You'd do that for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.61,0:04:22.89,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, I'm the organization's handyman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.04,0:04:24.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.70,0:04:28.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,are the two of you here today for a meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.79,0:04:31.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai just happened to be \Nhere when I walked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.43,0:04:33.26,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I just had a feeling I'd run into you two
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.40,0:04:35.90,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,if I came here tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.63,0:04:38.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Did you need something from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.85,0:04:40.16,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing really.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.95,0:04:41.86,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I just thought
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.03,0:04:46.65,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,tonight might become the \Nusual night if I did come.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.25,0:04:48.44,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.28,0:04:52.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,What are we toasting?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.22,0:04:54.72,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Anything's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.10,0:04:57.18,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really need a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.47,0:05:00.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,To the stray dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.48,0:05:08.95,Stray Dogs - Default,DA,0000,0000,0000,,To the stray dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.75,0:05:15.57,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ango, do you have a camera \Nin your bag by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.79,0:05:18.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, though it's for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.34,0:05:21.10,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a photo to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.26,0:05:22.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,To remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.29,0:05:23.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Remember what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.80,0:05:27.04,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That the three of us were gathered here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.32,0:05:29.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,But the three of us are \Nalways drinking here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.37,0:05:32.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,As the executive wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.57,0:05:35.48,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you take a good photo of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.81,0:05:37.95,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Taking it from this angle \Nmakes me look more manly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.40,0:05:41.02,sign_8114_134_Dazai_Osamu_,Sign 0541,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai Osamu
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.75,0:05:41.02,sign_8114_133_Ability___No_Lon,Sign 0541,0000,0000,0000,,Ability: \NNo Longer \NHuman
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.15,0:05:43.73,sign_8180_136_Sakaguchi__Ango_,Sign 0542,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaguchi \NAngo
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:43.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need {\i1}my{\i0} photo taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.42,0:05:43.73,sign_8180_137_Ability__Discour,Sign 0542,0000,0000,0000,,Ability: Discourse\Non Decadence
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.86,0:05:46.45,sign_8245_138_Oda__Sakunosuke,Sign 0545,0000,0000,0000,,Oda \NSakunosuke
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.13,0:05:46.45,sign_8275_138_Ability___Flawle,Sign 0545,0000,0000,0000,,Ability:\N Flawless
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.22,0:05:49.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want photos all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.40,0:05:51.17,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I just feel like if we don't do it now,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.17,0:05:57.24,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,there'll be nothing left to show \Nthat we hung out like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.60,0:06:00.65,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku, the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.44,0:06:07.31,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,And it turned out just like he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.84,0:06:10.64,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,That day became the last \Ntime that we could record
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:15.76,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,the invisible something we shared \Nbetween us in a photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.13,0:06:22.44,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Because one of us died soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.11,0:06:28.03,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,The lowest-ranking member would never
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.38,0:06:31.80,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,enter the Port Mafia headquarters \Nunder normal circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.64,0:06:37.30,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,No one knows what {\i0}he{\i1} wants from me,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:41.26,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,but, as far as this organization is \Nconcerned, his word is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.68,0:06:48.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Oda.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.90,0:06:52.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I am here because I received \Na summons from the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.61,0:07:00.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Oda.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.39,0:07:07.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Boss, it's Oda.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.99,0:07:08.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.04,0:07:10.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Elise-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.63,0:07:12.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Please wear the dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.39,0:07:13.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Just for a little bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:15.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Just put it on for a quick second!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:16.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.07,0:07:17.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.31,0:07:19.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Elise-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.13,0:07:20.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Please try it on, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.28,0:07:22.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I put a lot of thought into picking it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.87,0:07:25.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Look at these crimson frills!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.20,0:07:27.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,They're like flower petals!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.16,0:07:28.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll look great in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.00,0:07:31.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,I don't dislike pretty clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.27,0:07:33.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,But I hate your desperation, Rintaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:34.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:37.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I came under your orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.49,0:07:52.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,So, Oda-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.61,0:07:53.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.55,0:07:56.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,You did not see anything, understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.01,0:07:59.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I did not see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.45,0:08:01.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You made time for someone like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.14,0:08:05.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,even though you were busy getting a \Nyoung girl to change her clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.35,0:08:07.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you call me here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.72,0:08:08.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:12.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.88,0:08:15.17,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I called you here for one \Nreason and one reason alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.39,0:08:17.64,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I need you to find someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.64,0:08:19.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Find someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.13,0:08:21.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You're asking me, an ordinary member?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.90,0:08:24.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard good things about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.19,0:08:27.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I want to ask you specifically \Nto carry out this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.29,0:08:32.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,The missing person is Sakaguchi Ango-kun,\N an intelligence officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.60,0:08:37.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Ango-kun went missing last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.06,0:08:39.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,He never got home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.23,0:08:41.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,He may have chosen to vanish \Nof his own free will,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.63,0:08:45.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,or he may have been abducted. \NWe do not know which is the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.16,0:08:50.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,As you well know, Ango-kun is a \NPort Mafia intelligence officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.28,0:08:53.17,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,His head is full of secrets \Nthat would be enough
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.17,0:08:56.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,to crush us if he were to sell \Nthem to other organizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.01,0:08:59.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.63,0:09:01.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that were not the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.34,0:09:04.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Ango-kun is a competent and \Nimportant staff member to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.52,0:09:06.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I want to help him if \Nsomething has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.85,0:09:09.53,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Silver Oracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.92,0:09:11.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.79,0:09:13.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Show this to anyone in the organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.10,0:09:15.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,and you'll receive some form of assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.11,0:09:18.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,You can even order executives around.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.22,0:09:23.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that you have personal relations \Nwith an executive named Dazai-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.20,0:09:27.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,A friendship that surpasses \Nhierarchical bounds, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.99,0:09:30.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,His capabilities are astounding.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.66,0:09:32.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,In four, five years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.55,0:09:35.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he'll have killed me \Nto sit on the throne himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:42.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Oda-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.66,0:09:44.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:50.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Rumors have it that you've never killed \Nanyone with that gun of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:51.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.70,0:09:56.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Are you commanding me as the leader \Nof our organization to respond?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.41,0:09:59.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's a personal question. \NJust simple curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.54,0:10:02.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Then I prefer not to answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.10,0:10:07.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.41,0:10:08.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.41,0:10:12.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I await good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:20.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Ensure that the city police \Ndo not hear of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.06,0:10:20.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Call the cleaners, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.40,0:10:21.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,They need to transport the bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.62,0:10:25.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Find out if these three have families.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.72,0:10:29.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,If they do, I'll contact them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.62,0:10:32.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Also, an executive will be here shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.72,0:10:34.82,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.10,0:10:36.33,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on just one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.33,0:10:39.03,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to clear this difficult level.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.56,0:10:41.30,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap! He's ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.30,0:10:42.91,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Take this attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.91,0:10:44.05,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, he dodged it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.05,0:10:46.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai-dono, thank you for taking \Nthe trouble to come out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.55,0:10:49.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Our armory guards were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.00,0:10:50.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while since we last
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.92,0:10:53.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,had anyone reckless enough to \Ntarget a Port Mafia armory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.26,0:10:57.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Each died on the spot after being hit with\Nbetween ten and twenty 9mm rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.30,0:11:00.36,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Firearms were taken from the armory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.36,0:11:01.60,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll go take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.60,0:11:02.77,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of this, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:05.20,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.98,0:11:07.44,Stray Dogs - Top,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,I-I wouldn't know what to do right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:09.87,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This many rounds that went \Nclean through the bodies...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.44,0:11:10.52,Stray Dogs - Top,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Which buttons do I press?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.87,0:11:11.93,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That means a sub-machine gun \Nwas used at close range.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.75,0:11:14.32,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The assailants were pretty skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.54,0:11:16.19,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting my hopes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.67,0:11:18.68,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Do we have surveillance \Nfootage of the warehouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.21,0:11:23.39,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They just look like \Nvagrants at first glance,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.39,0:11:25.71,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,but they must be well-trained soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.43,0:11:29.58,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They are careful about covering \Neach others' blind spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:31.88,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Still, why take on this appearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.97,0:11:36.27,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hirotsu-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.27,0:11:38.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,I have no excuse to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.65,0:11:41.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,If you give me another \Nchance, I will surely—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.39,0:11:42.94,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Do you recognize this gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.33,0:11:46.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,It's an old model.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.01,0:11:47.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,It's older than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.10,0:11:52.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's a Graugeist. \NAn old European pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.29,0:11:56.69,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I saw this gun last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.14,0:12:07.46,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That means they attacked me right \Nbefore they hit the armory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.23,0:12:10.10,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been a distraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.14,0:12:13.68,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.13,0:12:17.54,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They're a far more interesting \Nbunch than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.37,0:12:24.17,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hirotsu-san, they hit one of the \NPort Mafia's best storage units.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.36,0:12:27.48,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They used the official passcode to get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.75,0:12:30.87,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's only known to members who \Nare sub-executives and higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.09,0:12:33.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Could it mean that we have a traitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.39,0:12:37.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Hirotsu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't we know who's behind these attacks?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.58,0:12:42.75,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,My subordinates tortured a hostage \Nfrom yesterday to make him talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.13,0:12:47.80,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,but he seized an opportunity to kill himself \Nusing a suicide pill hidden in his back tooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.39,0:12:50.30,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But we did manage to learn one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.29,0:12:53.58,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The organization's name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.96,0:12:57.00,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,{Eyecatch}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.96,0:12:57.00,sign_18557_275_Episode_13___The,Sign 1254,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 13 \N The Dark Age
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.71,0:12:56.17,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Mimic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.33,0:13:07.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,So Ango lives in a hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.81,0:13:30.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaguchi Ango...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:33.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,An intelligence officer with the Port Mafia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.35,0:13:37.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious intellectual,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.51,0:13:41.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,no one knew who you really were.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.63,0:13:46.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.53,0:13:54.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,A ventilation shaft?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.30,0:14:24.64,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,A sniper, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.35,0:14:32.36,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.36,0:14:35.64,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That's rare, getting a call from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.64,0:14:36.65,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I was targeted by a sniper.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.65,0:14:37.93,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,In Ango's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.25,0:14:39.92,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going after the sniper now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.92,0:14:42.39,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,He's firing from a building across \Nthe Secondhand Books Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.62,0:14:45.21,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,So you want me to cut his escape route off?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.41,0:14:48.05,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I have the Silver Oracle on hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.24,0:14:48.92,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,If you need me to, I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.92,0:14:50.02,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's no need.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.19,0:14:54.71,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Don't push yourself too hard\N until I get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.56,0:15:03.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.92,0:15:06.69,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,He was waiting for me \Ninstead of trying to run?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.77,0:15:09.59,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,He must be after this safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.57,0:15:16.07,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku, duck!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.64,0:15:30.54,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite the troublemaker, Odasaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.44,0:15:37.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You could have easily killed these \Nguys in an instant, if you wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.47,0:15:41.36,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,My ability, Flawless,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.36,0:15:44.52,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,allows me to see five, six \Nseconds into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.33,0:15:49.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You killed them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.84,0:15:53.05,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Not like we would've gotten any \Ninformation if we'd taken them hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.37,0:15:58.27,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,After all, they love the \Ntaste of their poison pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.56,0:16:00.91,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.29,0:16:03.67,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That's not why you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.29,0:16:07.57,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But they are trained combat professionals.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.87,0:16:10.55,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Even you would've been unable \Nto avoid killing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.17,0:16:14.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I would've ended up \Ndead if you hadn't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.75,0:16:16.33,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Oda Sakunosuke...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.78,0:16:20.52,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,A curious Port Mafia member \Nwho refuses to kill anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.52,0:16:22.29,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,no matter what the circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.90,0:16:25.30,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that troublesome creed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.48,0:16:28.81,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,you're being used as an errand \Nboy by the organization
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.21,0:16:31.15,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,despite your considerable capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.40,0:16:35.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that complaint a million times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.80,0:16:37.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, about this attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.08,0:16:40.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.13,0:16:42.22,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Look at his waist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.69,0:16:44.96,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,He's slinging an old pistol, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.16,0:16:47.49,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's called a Graugeist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.79,0:16:49.77,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Given that it's an old European pistol,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.77,0:16:52.26,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,it has low firing rate and accuracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.26,0:16:55.93,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,So it'd only serve to fire warning \Nshots in a narrow alley like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.31,0:17:01.59,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That pistol probably serves \Nas their emblem of some sort,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.39,0:17:05.36,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,to indicate who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.59,0:17:07.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,And who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.66,0:17:08.78,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Mimic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.78,0:17:09.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Mimic?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.18,0:17:12.76,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still investigating the specifics.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.76,0:17:16.27,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe we'll find something \Nout from the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.27,0:17:18.29,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,that they had a sniper watching Ango's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.79,0:17:21.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,They wanted to retrieve this safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.22,0:17:22.10,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,A safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.35,0:17:24.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,It was in Ango's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.09,0:17:26.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,But there was no key, and I can't open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.43,0:17:29.00,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.27,0:17:32.86,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.80,0:17:34.79,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Let me try.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.72,0:17:39.52,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Opened it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.82,0:17:41.65,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,He's sure clever with his hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.45,0:17:45.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.05,0:17:47.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.29,0:17:50.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You said this gun was their emblem, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.41,0:17:53.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,A sign of who they are...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.57,0:17:55.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,If Ango has one, it means...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.18,0:17:58.37,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This alone is inconclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.57,0:18:01.79,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Ango may have taken this gun from them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.17,0:18:07.68,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,or they may have planted \Nthis to implicate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.78,0:18:11.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.81,0:18:13.35,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But, Odasaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.86,0:18:16.17,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you one thing I've noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.69,0:18:18.90,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, when we were drinking at the bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.90,0:18:21.02,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Ango said he was on his way \Nback from a deal, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.50,0:18:23.17,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.89,0:18:24.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.12,0:18:26.49,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You saw his bag, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.06,0:18:29.80,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,From top to bottom, it had \Ncigarettes, a folding umbrella,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.80,0:18:32.70,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,a camera, and his prize, the antique watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.39,0:18:37.22,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The umbrella had been used, \Nand it was wrapped in cloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.81,0:18:40.81,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And his work trip was to Tokyo, \Nwhere it had rained.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.00,0:18:43.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,So his umbrella was wet because \Nit was raining where he went.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.67,0:18:45.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,What's odd about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.46,0:18:49.38,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Ango supposedly went there in his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.66,0:18:52.28,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,When did he use the umbrella, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.68,0:18:54.36,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't before the deal,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.51,0:18:57.29,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,because the umbrella was \Non top of the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.44,0:18:59.12,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And it wasn't after the deal, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.26,0:19:00.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.40,0:19:04.69,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The umbrella was wet enough that it wasn't \Nused for a mere two or three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.39,0:19:08.42,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been used in the rain \Nfor a good thirty minutes or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.80,0:19:11.11,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But despite supposedly being \Nin the rain for so long,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.11,0:19:14.04,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,his shoes and pants were dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.73,0:19:17.91,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,If his deal was at eight and \Nwe met at the bar at ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.16,0:19:22.20,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,two hours weren't enough for \Nhis shoes and pants to dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.20,0:19:24.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he changed clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.51,0:19:26.06,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,He drove me home in his car,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.06,0:19:30.02,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,but I didn't see any change \Nof clothes or shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.48,0:19:34.16,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I think Ango didn't go to a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.16,0:19:35.48,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,He met someone in the rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.94,0:19:38.27,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,spoke to them for about thirty minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.27,0:19:40.73,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,and then killed some time \Nbefore coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.30,0:19:43.76,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Intelligence officers like \NAngo sometimes choose
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.76,0:19:47.66,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,a rainy road for their secret meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.88,0:19:50.25,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's more secure than an indoor \Nspace for classified talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.66,0:19:53.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Ango is the Port Mafia's \Nclassified intelligence officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.07,0:19:57.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Of course he'd have one or two meetings \Nhe couldn't tell anyone about!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.37,0:19:59.26,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Then he could've just said \Nthat he couldn't tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.61,0:20:05.32,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,If he had, both you and I wouldn't \Nhave asked any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.20,0:20:07.27,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.44,0:20:10.29,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,He's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.73,0:20:13.75,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, he even made up an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.75,0:20:16.23,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What was the reason that he had to go \Nto such lengths to hide that meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.36,0:20:26.58,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you have commendable spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:31.68,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth, \NI hold you all in awe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.93,0:20:35.99,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,No other organization has managed \Nto face the Port Mafia head-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.99,0:20:36.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.97,0:20:37.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.97,0:20:45.36,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you can see the joy in my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.04,0:20:49.04,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,With just a slight press of your finger,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.30,0:20:52.56,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,you can give me what I desire most.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.89,0:20:56.58,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,My only fear is that \Nyou'll miss your target.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.85,0:20:58.38,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.38,0:21:00.09,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're a sniper, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.90,0:21:01.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.88,0:21:03.86,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, you'll be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.32,0:21:07.32,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,At least try to kill one of the \Nenemy executives before you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.43,0:21:08.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Dazai.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:12.37,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Please, take me with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.47,0:21:16.70,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Wake me from this oxidizing \Nworld of a dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.70,0:21:17.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.70,0:21:32.07,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to shock you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.15,0:21:34.59,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It was great acting, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.06,0:21:36.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Acting?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.51,0:21:38.84,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I knew he'd miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.76,0:21:42.80,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,His left cheek had the imprint \Nfrom the sniper's rifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.90,0:21:44.77,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, he is left-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.29,0:21:47.58,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,He was using his non-dominant right hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.69,0:21:50.74,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,and he was so unsteady that \Nhe could barely stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.02,0:21:53.39,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And with that old pistol?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.39,0:21:56.60,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't have succeeded unless he had the \Ngun pressed up right against my forehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.64,0:22:03.21,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you'd do something if I bought enough \Ntime with talk to tire his arm out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.21,0:22:04.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Just stop, Dazai.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.72,0:22:05.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.54,0:22:09.38,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.82,0:22:16.18,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Please find Ango.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.22,0:22:20.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
